        <TextBlock x:Name="Paragraph" HorizontalAlignment="Left" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="5,25,0,0" FontFamily="Bebas Kai" FontSize="16" Width="421"><Run Text="The following rules are for c++ that we must follow when naming variables:"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="1. Variables can only be made up of letters, digits, and underscores."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="2. Variables can't start with a digit, they must begin with a letter or underscore."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="3. Variables can't be a reserved word (e.g., if, else, while, for)."/><LineBreak/></TextBlock>


